Atlas Obscura|Joshua Foer, Dylan Thuras,Ella Morton|Workman|A richly documented ultimate explorer's guide to more than 700 hidden marvels, events and curiosities around the world.
Humans Of New York: Stories|Brandon Stanton|St. Martin's|More photographs, this time accompanied by interviews, from the creator of the blog and the book “Humans of New York.”
The Road To Little Dribbling|Bill Bryson|Anchor|An American expatriate travels around his adopted country, Britain.
Humans Of New York|Brandon Stanton|St. Martin's|Four hundred color photos of New Yorkers, with brief commentary. Originally published in 2013.
Sully|Chesley B Sullenberger III with Jeffrey Zaslow|Morrow/HarperCollins|A memoir by the pilot who made an emergency landing on the Hudson River in 2009. Originally published as “Highest Duty” in 2009. The basis for the 2016 movie.
Destinations Of A Lifetime|the staff of National Geographic|National Geographic Society|A photographic tour of 225 global destinations.
Speaking American|Josh Katz|Houghton Mifflin Harcourt|The creator of the New York Times dialect quiz provides a guide to how words are pronounced in different parts of the country.
Wild|Cheryl Strayed|Knopf|An account of the life-changing 1,100-mile solo hike along the Pacific Crest Trail in 1995. Originally published in 2012 and a 2014 movie.
Lion|Saroo Brierley|NAL|The author was lost on a train in India at age 5, then adopted by a couple in Australia; he searched for and found his birth family as an adult. Originally published in 2014 as “A Long Way Home” and the basis for the 2016 movie.
Nonstop Metropolis|Rebecca Solnit,Joshua Jelly-Schapiro|University of California|Essays and 26 imaginative maps celebrate New York City.
